Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.45,0:07:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this sunset was what you were waiting for
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.38,0:07:57.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.45,0:08:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just like you to do something like this\NI like things like this too
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.33,0:08:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.56,0:08:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So let's hurry and solve the case, bring him along!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.36,0:08:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It smears the world in blood.\NThe death throes of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.52,0:08:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder how many more times I'll get to see
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.92,0:08:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thi sad color...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.03,0:08:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, who is it that solved the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.40,0:08:47.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you did, Mrs. Kanno?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.84,0:08:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.34,0:08:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, sonny?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.01,0:08:55.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep! I've figured it all out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.48,0:08:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who took the hanging scroll and where it is too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.55,0:09:02.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hint is the altar of the dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.67,0:09:06.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the thief took the hanging scroll and fled,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.75,0:09:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the thief accidentally bumped into the doll altar and the dolls fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.09,0:09:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then when putting the dolls back on the steps the position
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.69,0:09:15.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lied) of the Emperor and Empress were reversed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.23,0:09:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why we searched Mr.\NTsumagari's room
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.17,0:09:22.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of all the four people that have a motive for stealing the hanging scroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.77,0:09:26.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,only he doesn't know how to line the dolls up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.97,0:09:29.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's just the opposite!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.14,0:09:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Opposite?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.08,0:09:32.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a good look at the altar!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.81,0:09:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you compare it to the time when we
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.78,0:09:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iined the dolls up before the burglar broke in,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.78,0:09:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a -0-1e--0 S-are a )I out of position, and except for the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.49,0:09:43.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Emperor and Empress, all the dolls are in the correct position!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.56,0:09:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he rights
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.59,0:09:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.13,0:09:51.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked the position of the dolls after the children lined them in place
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.87,0:09:53.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the burglar bumped into t he altar with enough
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.87,0:09:57.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,impact to drop the Emperor and the Empress.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.04,0:09:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other dolls and accessories would have fell too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.58,0:10:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the person didn't know how to line the dolls up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.28,0:10:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is no way that the dolls would be\NIined up as perfectly as this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.11,0:10:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the burglar did actually line the\NEmperor and Empress up wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.82,0:10:14.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if it's not a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.19,0:10:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if this is the traditional way that dolls
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.69,0:10:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,used to be lined up in ancient times in Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.46,0:10:22.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The traditional way?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.53,0:10:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.00,0:10:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,4 Aro 1\NOriginally in Japan, the honorable seat was
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.93,0:10:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to the left and the\NIower seat to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.70,0:10:32.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the person who is higher in rank used to stand on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.47,0:10:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,AS you can see, the elderly\NMinister of the left is on the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.68,0:10:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,¢df6K5CF whereas, the young Minister of the right is on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.41,0:10:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the Emperor and\NEmpress in accordance
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.75,0:10:44.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to this tradition of men being higher in rank than women
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.29,0:10:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the Emperor is on the left and the\NEmpress is on the right
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.89,0:10:53.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan, you're wrong!\NThe man's on the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.73,0:10:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, like I've been telling you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.06,0:10:58.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of the 'dolls the\NEmperor as to tfuveft of the Empress!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.53,0:10:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.04,0:11:05.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, all the dolls decorated in show windows are opposite from the altar there
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.84,0:11:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because this is Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.21,0:11:10.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the Meiji Restoration when the western custom of the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.61,0:11:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,right side being the honorable position entered Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.88,0:11:17.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the position of the Emperor during the coronation also changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.62,0:11:22.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so followed the doll industry of Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.29,0:11:26.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure know a lot, don't you sonny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.23,0:11:30.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep, I love to check out things like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.77,0:11:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.47,0:11:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been meaning to ask you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.31,0:11:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you always talk childish only when you talk to adults?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.24,0:11:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as you're fawning, on them or something
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.25,0:11:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.91,0:11:51.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather, you give me the creeps.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.72,0:11:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay okay, you want me to act natural like always huh satisfied!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.09,0:11:58.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like the way you talk, it's cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.23,0:12:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it's kind of girlish, it's sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.13,0:12:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, who's the burglar, sonny?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.47,0:12:09.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes. So, the burglar is someone
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.04,0:12:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who knows how the dolls used to lined up in olden times
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.61,0:12:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either Grandma Kanno or appraiser Mr. Mie!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.65,0:12:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When grandma was still a child the old way
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.47,0:12:32.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of lining up the dolls was widespread.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.87,0:12:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, she's originally from Kyoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.22,0:12:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are many homes in\NKyoto that take traditional
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.49,0:12:40.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,seriously and stick to the traditional way of doing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.06,0:12:43.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably learned to line the dolls up the traditional way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.10,0:12:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mie should also know the traditional way of lining the dolls up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.94,0:12:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he knows that those dolls are from Kyoto
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.01,0:12:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's not inconceivable that he would line them up that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.48,0:13:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I does he know that those dolls are from « oto?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.91,0:13:04.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Setsuko told him so
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.25,0:13:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the dolls from\NKyoto have accessories
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.02,0:13:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that are different from the dolls in To v0
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.99,0:13:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that a professional would be able to tell right off the bat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.16,0:13:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-So, which one of them is the burglar and where is the hanging scroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.86,0:13:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you don't know who it is again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.30,0:13:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know who it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.83,0:13:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Ayumi gave me the hint, steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.44,0:13:25.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Steps, don't tell me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.57,0:13:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.77,0:13:29.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The burglar climbed-the altar as if they were steps and hid the hanging scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.98,0:13:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,scroll in the cabinet above the closet!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.68,0:13:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, when the burglar did so, some of the dolls were kicked by the burglar's foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.45,0:13:38.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the dolls fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.89,0:13:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Genta, be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.39,0:13:46.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the hanging scroll is probably still in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.53,0:13:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not here...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.36,0:13:52.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not there. In the back, behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.50,0:13:57.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A steps like this altar was brought out and the hanging scroll was hid in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.64,0:14:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the dolls fell when the altar was moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.14,0:14:04.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The burglar wasn't aware that if you go inside the closet like this
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.94,0:14:07.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it would've been easy to hide the scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.38,0:14:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The box for the doll set is here, but there's nothing else
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.99,0:14:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the dolls fell when the burglar fled, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.29,0:14:21.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no dolls were dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.16,0:14:26.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The burglar took all the dolls away from the altar deliberately.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.03,0:14:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to hide the hanging scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.27,0:14:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Took the dolls away?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.77,0:14:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that the hanging scroll is!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.48,0:14:37.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, help me move the dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.31,0:14:38.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.55,0:14:44.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's a convenient place to hide paper things such as hanging scrolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.78,0:14:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And yet, it's asplace that's hard to find even if you search for it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.52,0:14:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.79,0:14:57.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,behind the red cloth of the altar';.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.70,0:14:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.73,0:15:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A place that is not visible unless all the dolls are moved,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.70,0:15:07.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is hard to reach, in other words, hard to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.34,0:15:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, Ayumi mentioned that the dolls looked sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.58,0:15:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because the this wooden plate that is on the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.31,0:15:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,top of the hanging scroll was underneath
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.28,0:15:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you put-the wooden place above this laughing doll,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.22,0:15:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it tilts forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.82,0:15:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And its facial expression changes, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.62,0:15:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, that's why its laughing face looked a bit different!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.49,0:15:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why is it placed reversed?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.80,0:15:38.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thick plate that is attached under the hanging scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.00,0:15:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,cannot be covered with just the red cloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.58,0:15:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-W-Wait! If the burglar hid the hanging scroll in a place like this, it means
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.48,0:15:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, after the police leave, the burglar can
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.38,0:15:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,pretend to put the dolls away and also retrieve the hanging scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.09,0:15:58.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only grandma is capable of doing this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.16,0:16:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Grandma?\NYou have have to b joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.60,0:16:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, after we left to go shopping and she was at home all alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.00,0:16:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably came up with the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.07,0:16:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of hiding the hanging scroll and messing up the room
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.31,0:16:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make it look like a burglar broke In!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.74,0:16:19.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then she goes up shopping herself
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.55,0:16:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make it look as if a burglar broke in while she was out...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.75,0:16:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But. I wonder if that granny would even come across the idea of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.15,0:16:32.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a burglar opening the veranda window and breaking in through the roof?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.89,0:16:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, they broadcast a lot of those kinds of programs on TV
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.96,0:16:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,recently that I'm sure grandma had seen them too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.57,0:16:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1.l guess so...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.27,0:16:44.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why would she do a thing like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.84,0:16:46.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me you did it, granny!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.81,0:16:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You tried to get insurance money for it after making it look as if it were stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.41,0:16:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would never do something so evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This hanging scroll is the protective god of the Kanno family
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.05,0:17:01.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Protective god?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.55,0:17:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's why I decided to hide it for now, and after my son returns from work
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.66,0:17:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was going to show him the\NThunder God and tell him about it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.17,0:17:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is, not to repeat the mistake that I made
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.47,0:17:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Repeat?\NDon't tell me that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.14,0:17:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, We originally had the hanging scroll of the Wind God here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.11,0:17:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was found in the storeroom of my husband's parental home,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.50,0:17:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we're not sure where it came from but
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.62,0:17:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband used to always say
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.12,0:17:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are the Kanno family, so this hanging scroll is most likely our protective god
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.60,0:17:45.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it.- the Wind God and Thunder God are
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.33,0:17:48.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the guardian deity of the 12 handed Goddess of Mercy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.67,0:17:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When my son got married,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.44,0:17:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we were having trouble getting money together to buy this condo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.41,0:17:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I decided to sell the Wind God scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.31,0:18:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sold it secretly while my husband was on a company trip
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.32,0:18:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.82,0:18:10.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the passenger liner that my husband was on board sunk
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.86,0:18:15.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when they encountered a typhoon that was just as if the Wind GodMhad-created
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.60,0:18:21.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then are you saying that the cursed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.73,0:18:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wind God scroll made its rounds and came to me
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.44,0:18:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is not cursed .
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.51,0:18:31.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like they say the Girls' Festival dolls were originally placed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.11,0:18:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,by the pillow of the child as a protective charm to ward off evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.18,0:18:39.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likewise, every time that hanging scroll is stained or soiled I feel
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.16,0:18:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that it may be warding off misfortune that may befall our family for us
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.53,0:18:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, please do not lay a hand on that Thunder God scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.11,0:19:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that we know it is not only very valuable, but also has additional benefits,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.55,0:19:12.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the more we wouldn't mind risking our lives for it, right Mr. Tsumagari?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.39,0:19:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Nos I'm totally satisfied with only the Wind God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.26,0:19:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forget all of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.03,0:19:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, how disappointing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.20,0:19:27.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However. I will be back again later, rs, anno.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.10,0:19:28.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.61,0:19:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To teach you an easy way to store it...
